%F A052889 Let A be the upper Hessenberg matrix of order n defined by: A[i,i-1]=-1, A[i,j]=binomial(j-1,i-1), (i<=j), and A[i,j]=0 otherwise. Then, for n>=1, a(n)=(-1)^(n-1)*coeff(charpoly(A,x),x). - _Milan Janjic_, Jul 08 2010
